BP raises LPG prices to $ 323 and $ 265 a tonne . BP announced on Friday that it has raised its liquefied petroleum gas ( LPG ) prices , the BP Agreed Price ( BPAP ) , for December to $ 323 a tonne for propane and $ 265 a tonne for butane . This is a rise of $ 59 a tonne for propane and $ 32 . 50 for butane . - - London Newsroom , + 44 171 542 6412 
